  "original_title": "\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0ba9\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0baf\u0bcb\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd : \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc7\u0bb7\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0baa\u0bca\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0bb8\u0bcd \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b89\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0baa\u0bbf\u0ba3\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0b9a\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0bae\u0bbe \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b8e\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Rambukkana shooting: Attorney General opposes bail for former senior superintendent of police",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "Police in riot gear stormed a rally in Rambukkana, Kegalle on Friday, removing hundreds of protesters by truck.",
        "The announcement was made by Deputy Solicitor General Janaka Bandara on behalf of the Attorney General in the Main Court of Appeal.",
        "Respondent today (27) when a petition was filed seeking the issuance of a 'writ' order (writ) quashing the order of Kegalle Magistrate Vasana Navaratna to immediately arrest the police officer who ordered the shooting and the police officers involved in the shooting. Janaka Bandara announced this.",
        "Former Kegalle Senior Superintendent of Police K.P. The writ petition has been filed in the Court of Appeal on behalf of the police officers including Keerthiratne.",
        "In this context, the Court of Appeal of Maine directed the Inspector General of Police and the Director General of the CID, who have been named as defendants in the petition, to appear before the House on the 27th of this month.",
        "Accordingly, the writ petition was considered today in the presence of a panel of judges comprising Justices Sobitha Rajakaruna and Dhammika Kanepola of the Main Court of Appeal.",
        "President's Counsel Savannah Fernando and Deputy Solicitor General Janaka Bandara appeared for the petitioners.",
        "Presenting the case to the House, Presidential Counsel Savannah Fernando said that if the Attorney General declares that he has no objection to bailing out his service recipients, there is no need to take the case further.",
        "Deputy Solicitor General Janaka Bandara, who was present in the House, said that the Attorney General would issue an objection to grant bail to the petitioners.",
        "Accordingly, the court decided to continue the petition for further consideration and decided to hold further hearings on the 29th of next month."
      ],
